---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const pageTitle = "How SpeedRead Works - Five Speed Reading Modes";
const pageDescription = "Learn when to use flash RSVP, phrase, focus, bionic, or page reading. See how ORP alignment, punctuation-aware pacing, and local document processing work.";
const howToSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'HowTo',
  name: 'How to use SpeedRead',
  description: pageDescription,
  step: [
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', name: 'Bring in the material', text: 'Paste text, upload a supported document, scan an image, extract a public URL, or send a page from the Chrome extension.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', name: 'Choose the right reading mode', text: 'Choose Flash, Phrase, Focus, Bionic, or Page based on how much context the material requires.' },
    { '@type': 'HowToStep', name: 'Adjust as you read', text: 'Pause, rewind, change WPM, switch themes, or enable Audio Sync without reloading the document.' },
  ],
};
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <section class="method-hero">
    <div class="container method-hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="page-label">How SpeedRead works</p>
        <h1>One document.<br />The right amount of context.</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="method-hero-copy">
        <p>Speed reading is not a contest to show one word as fast as possible. SpeedRead lets you move between five views without losing your place, so the format can match the material.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/#importer-card">Try it with your text</a>
        <small>No account required. Your uploaded files are parsed in your browser.</small>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="method-explainer">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="orp-explainer">
        <div class="orp-demo" aria-label="Optimal recognition point example">
          <span>rea</span><strong>d</strong><span>ing</span>
          <i aria-hidden="true"></i>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Your eyes stay anchored in Flash mode.</h2>
          <p>Each word is split around its Optimal Recognition Point. The highlighted letter stays in one fixed position while the rest of the word moves around it. Punctuation and longer words receive extra time, so high WPM does not become a metronome that ignores meaning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mode-guide" aria-label="Reading mode guide">
        <article>
          <span>Fastest</span><h2>Flash</h2>
          <p>One word at a fixed point. Best for clearing familiar articles, newsletters and backlog items quickly.</p>
          <dl><div><dt>Context</dt><dd>One word</dd></div><div><dt>Starting pace</dt><dd>300-400 WPM</dd></div></dl>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Balanced</span><h2>Phrase</h2>
          <p>Three-word groups keep short grammatical relationships together. Use it when single-word RSVP feels too fragmented.</p>
          <dl><div><dt>Context</dt><dd>Three words</dd></div><div><dt>Starting pace</dt><dd>280-380 WPM</dd></div></dl>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Contextual</span><h2>Focus</h2>
          <p>The full paragraph remains visible while a focus highlight advances. It is the bridge between paced reading and a normal page.</p>
          <dl><div><dt>Context</dt><dd>Full paragraph</dd></div><div><dt>Starting pace</dt><dd>220-320 WPM</dd></div></dl>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Self-paced</span><h2>Bionic</h2>
          <p>Bold word beginnings provide visual anchors while you control the scan. Useful for reference material and rereading.</p>
          <dl><div><dt>Context</dt><dd>Full page</dd></div><div><dt>Pace</dt><dd>You control it</dd></div></dl>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Most context</span><h2>Page</h2>
          <p>A clean document view for careful study, comparison and sections you need to quote or inspect precisely.</p>
          <dl><div><dt>Context</dt><dd>Full page</dd></div><div><dt>Pace</dt><dd>You control it</dd></div></dl>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="honest-use">
    <div class="container honest-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>Use speed reading as a first pass.</h2>
        <p>Newsletters, industry reports, meeting notes, saved articles and long email threads are strong fits. Start in Phrase or Focus if the topic is new, then move faster once the vocabulary becomes familiar.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>Slow down when precision matters.</h2>
        <p>Contracts, equations, unfamiliar technical writing and anything you must cite exactly deserve a lower WPM or the full Page view. Comprehension is the objective. Speed is only a control.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="method-steps">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>From source to focused reading in three steps.</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><span>1</span><div><strong>Bring in the material</strong><p>Paste text, upload PDF, EPUB or TXT, scan an image, extract a public URL, or send a page from the Chrome extension.</p></div></li>
        <li><span>2</span><div><strong>Choose context before speed</strong><p>Pick Flash, Phrase, Focus, Bionic or Page. Start at a comfortable pace instead of chasing the highest number.</p></div></li>
        <li><span>3</span><div><strong>Adjust as the material changes</strong><p>Pause, rewind, change WPM, switch themes or enable Audio Sync. Your reading position stays with the document.</p></div></li>
      </ol>
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/#importer-card">Start reading now</a>
    </div>
  </section>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(howToSchema)} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .method-hero { padding: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 8rem) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .method-hero-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.4fr) minmax(280px, 0.75fr); gap: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 7rem); align-items: end; }
  .page-label { margin: 0 0 1rem; color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 700; }
  h1 { max-width: 13ch; margin: 0; font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem); line-height: 0.94; letter-spacing: -0.04em; }
  .method-hero-copy p { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 1.08rem; }
  .method-hero-copy .btn { margin-top: 1.25rem; }
  .method-hero-copy small { display: block; margin-top: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-text-subtle); }
  .method-explainer { padding: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem) 0; }
  .orp-explainer { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(280px, 0.8fr) minmax(0, 1fr); gap: clamp(2rem, 7vw, 6rem); align-items: center; padding-bottom: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem); }
  .orp-demo { position: relative; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr; align-items: center; min-height: 13rem; padding: 2rem; background: #090b12; color: white; border-radius: var(--radius-lg); font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 7vw, 5rem); font-weight: 700; }
  .orp-demo span:first-child { text-align: right; }
  .orp-demo strong { padding: 0.05em 0.09em; color: white; background: var(--color-primary); border-radius: var(--radius-xs); }
  .orp-demo i { position: absolute; left: 50%; top: 1rem; bottom: 1rem; width: 1px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.18); }
  .orp-explainer h2, .method-steps h2 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.8rem); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.04em; }
  .orp-explainer p { max-width: 62ch; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .mode-guide { border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .mode-guide article { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 7rem minmax(120px, 0.5fr) minmax(260px, 1.5fr) minmax(230px, 0.8fr); gap: 1.5rem; align-items: center; min-height: 8rem; padding: 1.25rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .mode-guide article > span { color: var(--color-primary); font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; }
  .mode-guide h2 { margin: 0; font-size: 1.5rem; }
  .mode-guide p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .mode-guide dl { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin: 0; }
  .mode-guide dt { color: var(--color-text-subtle); font-size: 0.72rem; }
  .mode-guide dd { margin: 0.2rem 0 0; color: var(--color-text); font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 700; }
  .honest-use { padding: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem) 0; background: var(--color-primary); color: white; }
  .honest-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 7rem); }
  .honest-use h2 { color: white; font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3.2rem); letter-spacing: -0.04em; }
  .honest-use p { max-width: 58ch; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); }
  .method-steps { padding: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem) 0; }
  .method-steps > .container { max-width: 920px; }
  .method-steps ol { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .method-steps li { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr; gap: 1rem; padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .method-steps li > span { color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 700; }
  .method-steps strong { display: block; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .method-steps p { max-width: 68ch; margin: 0.3rem 0 0; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .method-hero-grid, .orp-explainer, .honest-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .mode-guide article { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.75rem 1rem; }
    .mode-guide article > p, .mode-guide article > dl { grid-column: 1 / -1; }
    .orp-demo { min-height: 10rem; }
  }
</style>
